Call for Papers ( short version ) IJCAI- 97 Workshop on The Future of AI and the Internet August 24 , Nagoya , Japan
The aim of this workshop is to discuss the medium to long-term research agenda for Artificial Intelligence on the Internet . Workshop participants will be expected to take a position on the central question : "What aspect of AI will play an important role on the Internet in the next 5 - 10 years , and why ?" The workshop will take the shape of a debate on the current state , future promise , and overall importance of different research areas .
Electronic submissions , not longer than 10 pages ( if printed ) for full papers , or 3 pages for short position papers , are due by February 19 , 1997 . For more details and up-to-date information , please see the workshop homepage :
